<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY MARCY BLACK SIMPSON</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 1 dozen squares </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2 cups sweetened shredded coconut, divided </p><p class="no-indent">¼ cup butter </p><p class="no-indent">1 (16-ounce) bag marshmallows </p><p class="no-indent">⅔ cup caramel topping </p><p class="no-indent">10 cups puffed rice cereal </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 350°. Spread coconut evenly on a baking sheet. Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring once. Cool completely. Spray a 13x9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large stockpot, melt butter over medium heat. Add marshmallows and caramel. Cook, stirring constantly, for about 5 minutes or until marshmallows have melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and 1 cup toasted coconut. Press mixture into prepared baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup toasted coconut. Cool completely in pan before cutting into 12 squares.</p></div>
